# Riverpod State Management

## Allowed Providers
- Provider — computed/derived values
- StateProvider — simple mutable atoms
- NotifierProvider / AsyncNotifierProvider — complex state with methods
- FutureProvider — one-shot async data
- StreamProvider — reactive streams

## Rules
- State lives in providers, NEVER in widgets
- Use autoDispose unless explicit keepAlive is justified
- Use ref.watch() in build, ref.read() in callbacks, ref.listen() for side-effects
- Every async provider must handle loading/error/data via AsyncValue
- Use select() to minimize rebuilds
- Never use ref.read() in build — it won't rebuild on changes
- Provider families for parameterized providers

## Forbidden
- Provider package (use flutter_riverpod)
- BLoC/Cubit
- setState for business logic
- Mutable global variables
- Business logic inside Widget.build()
- Side-effects in build() — use ref.listen() instead
